page.title: 05FLOWERS AND TREES
page.content: {WILD FLOWERS}The flowers in this area range from beautiful Orchids to the more common Vetches and Speedwells. The most common woodland flower is the Bluebell, others include Primroses and Wood Anemones. Buttercups, Daisies and Cowslips dominate the meadow land.{ {TREES}There are a lot of trees in the area, both in woodland and garden. They are mainly deciduous, the most common being the Birch, Beech, Lime, Ash and Common Oak. Trees not native to England, such as Pines and Cedars, were planted when some of the area was parkland. Many trees are subject to preservation orders. { {SCRUB}This comprises various bushes such as blackberries and creepers such as Ivy. Other vegetation includes Sedge, Holly, Hawthorn, Hazel and Wood Club-rush.
